de.uni.bamberg.wiai.minf.forflow.datagenerator.controller
Enum XMLType

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<XMLType>
      de.uni.bamberg.wiai.minf.forflow.datagenerator.controller.XMLType
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<XMLType>
public enum XMLType
extends java.lang.Enum<XMLType>

The system uses a XMl file to initializing some parameters before the system starts the UI. While working with the application a tester might add some new elements or remove some of the old one. In both cases it's important for the startup file to reflect the changes properly. To indicate which part of the XML file has to change, to get synchronized with the user action, enumes are helpful.

Notice, this enumeration is stored at controller layer, because only controller has notice of the existence of it.

Enum Constant Detail

ARTEFACT

public static final XMLType ARTEFACT
tells that to < Artefact> element new child element are added or old ones are deleted, respectively. XML structure is something like this, where Type is a sub-child of Artefact. 
 < Artefact>
     < Type>< /Type>
 < /Artefact>
